<br>
Any item that drops from a mob which is turned in to another NPC as part of the completion of any class's Epic weapon.<br>
<br>
<br>
Vox/Naggy Policy<br>
<br>
1. Any Claw member that wishes to run a Vox/Naggy raid and to default a single piece of loot, Epic or otherwise, to another Claw Primary character will be permitted to do so as long as it is stated PRIOR to the start of the raid.<br>
<br>
2. In the case where additional Epic piece(s) drop outside one that may be defaulted to the raid leader, those Epic piece(s) will randomed in accordance per the raid leader's predetermined rules.<br>
<br>
Example:<br>
<br>
Tomar bravely leads a Vox raid to obtain an Eyepatch for himself.  In a show of bravado, Tomar solo kills Vox while the rest of the raid watches on and cheers.  In the discovered loot is a White Scale and a Pally Book.  Tomar, being the smart guy that he is, will have rules already set up ahead of time on the fair, non-defaulted distribution of these items.  Despite Tomar's bravery in singlehandedly slaying Vox, no Eyepatch drops.  Sorry, Tomar... better luck next time.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :evil --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/devil.gif ALT=":evil"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->    <br>
<br>
3. An order Vox/Naggy raid leadership will be determined by the Guild Leader from those people who wish to run these raids. The Guild Leader will maintain the priority list and will have final word in determining which main can have the next Vox/Naggy try.<br>
<br>
4. People on the Vox/Naggy priority list may elect to lower their position voluntarily should outside commitments or bad timing of a Vox/Naggy raid preclude them from being able to lead the raid. If this needs to occur, the Guild Leader must be notified and the next person in line will be asked to lead the raid.<br>
<br>
5. When it is your turn to run Vox/Naggy, you'll put your name in on the Bristlebane Event Calendar using the correct EC rules.  Please see the procedures on the EC boards or talk to Aradan in game to accomplish this correctly.<br>
<br>
6. Once a raid leader has won or lost, and fought his/her battle(s) against Vox/Naggy, that person will then be placed at the end of the line for running the next raid.<br>
<br>
7. Those characters just achieving Main status and who wish to run Vox/Naggy raids will be placed at the end of the line to await their turn.<br>
<br>
8. Alts and Mains are always free to run any non-Vox/Naggy raid they choose at any time using whatever loot rules they decide. Keep in mind when doing this that support from your fellow Guildmates may be determined on the fairness of the rules that are set up.<br>
<br>
-------------------------<br>
<br>
For the Master Main list, I will be setting up a thread which people can add their the name of their Main character as a reply to the thread.  I will remove the replys and add the names as I can.<br>
<br>
For the Vox/Naggy list there will be another thread that I'll keep open for a week.  All characters who are interested in running Vox/Naggy please sign up there and I'll create a priority list based on time served in Claw, Main/Alt status, level, and possibly other criteria.<br>
<br>
If you have any questions, please ask them on the New Policies Q&amp;A thread.  Thanks! <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub2.ezboard.com/uaradan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aradan</A> at: 11/2/01 4:41:58 pm<br></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafentherunningcharterdiscussion.showPrevMessage?topicID=47.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafentherunningcharterdiscussion.showNextMessage?topicID=47.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafentherunningcharterdiscussion.emailToFriend?topicID=47.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafentherunningcharterdiscussion.threadControl?topicID=47.topic><img src=http://www.clawofnagafen.com/boards/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafentherunningcharterdiscussion.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=47.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub148.ezboard.com/fthewordsofnagafentherunningcharterdiscussion.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=47.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub148.e